headline.print_headline: Going Way Back With Cubans, Tampa Leads Push Forward
headline.main: Going Way Back With Cubans, Tampa Leads Push Forward

snippet: The city sees itself as pivotal in efforts to rekindle diplomatic ties to Cuba, a move that runs counter to the anti-engagement orthodoxy of Miami and Florida’s government.
abstract: Tampa, Fla, is making strong effort to capitalize on Pres Obama's renewal of diplomatic relations with Cuba, positioning itself to reap both economic and cultural benefits of exchange; effort builds on over six generations of ties between Tampa and Cuba and runs counter to anti-engagement stance long held by government officials in Miami and Florida.
